# AWS Marketplace fulfillment URL — AWS POSTs x-amzn-marketplace-token in the
# request BODY (application/x-www-form-urlencoded), not as a query param.
# This MUST be a forced proxy (200!) so the POST method + body are forwarded
# to the Lambda. A plain rewrite to /index.html (no !) silently discards the
# POST body — the static SPA shell gets served but the token never arrives
# anywhere, which is what was causing the AWS Marketplace audit failure
# ("fulfillment URL... does not handle x-amzn-marketplace-token correctly").
/marketplace-redirect          https://9xyetu7zq3.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/prod/marketplace/resolve  200!

# SPA fallback — must be last
/*    /index.html   200
